HEADWORD: Bioplast
<hw>Bi"o*plast</hw> <pr>(-pl⟦acr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>bi`os</grk> life + <grk>pla`ssein</grk> to form.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A tiny mass of bioplasm, in itself a living unit
and having formative power, as a living white blood corpuscle;
bioblast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bioplastic</ent>⟦br⟧
